stylometry: It is difficult for excel to work with IF statements, or inter programming models, because it does not always read the actual statement and use it effectively in the algorithm. The algorithm is set to come within 5% of the "optimal" solution, which sometimes is not the true solution you may want. We have to consider logical upper limits when dealing with 0-1 models in excel. Excel reads maximums and minimums of a set of data, meaning that it can better compute the 0-1 of whether or not a line is open. The example that comes to mind is the hw problem I had that worked both ways with solver once, but I coud not get it to work with the IF statement any other times after, the logical upper limit took into consideration the maximum number of workers that needed and were feasible to put on a line.
